    "claim": "`manualEpochInit` skips the usual `!epochIsInitialized(...)` guard when `epochId == 0`, so any caller can overwrite `poolSize[token][0]` back to zero even after users already seeded that pool. Later epoch initialization copies the forged zero value forward while user balances and checkpoints stay non-zero.",
    "impact": "If the contract was live before `epoch1Start` (June 21, 2021) and users deposited during epoch 0, an attacker can wipe the base snapshot for epoch 1 and beyond. That can exclude those stakers from reward accounting and make later withdrawals revert on pool-size underflow, effectively locking funds until enough new deposits refill the pool.",
